LLM-unfriendly languages indeed face significant challenges in the coming years. The dominance of Python and related languages, such as JavaScript and TypeScript, highlights their adaptability and integration with AI tools. As for C/C++, while powerful, the increased reliance on automated bug detection and memory management can expose their weaknesses, leading to more errors that are harder to debug. Perl and PHP, being legacy-heavy, will likely see reduced use as modern, more predictable languages gain favor. Overall, while niche languages like MATLAB